Title: An Act to Fund the Operations of the University of Maine
Official Title: An Act to Fund the Operations of the University of Maine
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 3 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1012
S.P. 429 In Senate, March 13, 2025
Cooperative Extension Tick Laboratory
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on March 12, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Education and Cultural Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator FARRIN of Somerset.
Cosponsored by Senator: TIMBERLAKE of Androscoggin, Representative: GOLEK of
Harpswell.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 7 MRSA c. 421 is enacted to read:
3 CHAPTER 421
4 UNIVERSITY OF MAINE COOPERATIVE EXTENSION TICK LABORATORY
5 OPERATIONS FUND
6 §2481. Fund established
7 The University of Maine Cooperative Extension Tick Laboratory Operations Fund,
8 referred to in this chapter as "the fund," is established. The fund consists of revenues
9 received pursuant to Title 8, section 374, subsection 6 and any funds received as
10 contributions from private and public sources. The fund must be held separate and apart
11 from all other money, funds and accounts. Eligible investment earnings credited to the
12 assets of the fund become part of the assets of the fund. Any balance remaining in the fund
13 at the end of any fiscal year must be carried forward to the next fiscal year. The fund is
14 administered by the University of Maine Cooperative Extension.
15 §2482. Expenditures from fund; distribution
16 Funds in the fund must be distributed as provided under this section.
17 1. Funds received from State. All funds received from the State dedicated to the
18 fund must be expended on the operations of the University of Maine Cooperative Extension
19 tick laboratory or successor laboratory, including, but not limited to, supplies, educational
20 materials development, salaries, equipment and travel.
21 2. Funds received from private or public sources. All funds received from private
22 or public sources that were directed to the fund by the donating source must be spent on
23 the operations of the University of Maine Cooperative Extension tick laboratory or
24 successor laboratory, including, but not limited to, supplies, educational materials
25 development, salaries, equipment and travel.
26 Sec. 2. 8 MRSA §374, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
27 6. Tick laboratory lottery game. No later than January 30, 2026, the commission, in
28 consultation with the University of Maine Cooperative Extension, shall develop and initiate
29 a tick laboratory instant lottery game designed to raise funds for the University of Maine
30 Cooperative Extension Tick Laboratory Operations Fund established in Title 7, section
31 2481. Tickets for the instant lottery game established under this subsection must be sold
32 for $4 and must be changed by the commission periodically throughout the year. The
33 commission shall annually provide 50% of the net proceeds of the lottery game established
34 in accordance with this subsection to the University of Maine Cooperative Extension Tick
35 Laboratory Operations Fund and 50% to the General Fund.
36 Sec. 3. 8 MRSA §387, sub-§1, ¶C, as amended by PL 1995, c. 494, §5, is further
37 amended to read:
38 C. For payment to the General Fund; and
Page 1 - 132LR1367(01)
1 Sec. 4. 8 MRSA §387, sub-§1, ¶D, as amended by PL 2003, c. 414, Pt. B, §18 and
2 affected by c. 614, §9, is further amended to read:
3 D. For payment to the Maine Outdoor Heritage Fund pursuant to Title 12, section
4 10302.; and
5 Sec. 5. 8 MRSA §387, sub-§1, ¶E is enacted to read:
6 E. For payment to the University of Maine Cooperative Extension Tick Laboratory
7 Operations Fund pursuant to Title 7, section 2481.
8 Sec. 6. Report. By December 15, 2028, the State Liquor and Lottery Commission
9 shall submit a report to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
10 over lottery matters detailing the status of the tick laboratory instant lottery game
11 established pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 8, section 374, subsection 6,
12 including revenues received by the General Fund and the University of Maine Cooperative
13 Extension Tick Laboratory Operations Fund established in Title 7, section 2481. The joint
14 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over lottery matters may report
15 out legislation related to the report to the 134th Legislature in 2029.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill establishes the University of Maine Cooperative Extension Tick Laboratory
1188 Operations Fund and directs the State Liquor and Lottery Commission to develop and
1199 initiate a $4 instant lottery game to raise funds for the fund. The commission is required
2200 to submit a report by December 15, 2028 detailing the status of the instant lottery game to
2211 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over lottery matters,
2222 which may report out legislation related to the report to the 134th Legislature in 2029.
